message.content:
This session is being continued from a previous conversation that ran out of context. The summary below covers the earlier portion of the conversation.

Summary:
1. Primary Request and Intent:

The session continued from a prior conversation where the user ran 7 parallel agent sessions (WP-A through WP-G) implementing Revit 2026 parity features in bim-ai. Key requests in this session:

- Verify wave-1 agents finished cleanly and built on existing code rather than duplicating it
- Fix the tracker Summary Dashboard which was stale
- Schedule wave-2 agents by writing 7 self-contained prompts
- Monitor wave-2 progress and identify outstanding gaps
- **Directly implement the 2 items WP-D missed**: (1) Named locked 3D view lock toggle, (2) Walkthrough camera path animation — so the tracker is clean and wave-3 can be scheduled normally

2. Key Technical Concepts:

- bim-ai: browser-based BIM authoring tool (React + TypeScript + Three.js, Vite, Vitest) at `/Users/jhoetter/repos/bim-ai`
- Revit 2026 parity tracker: `spec/revit-parity/revit2026-parity-tracker.md`
- Wave system: agents run in 7 parallel terminals; each WP has a self-contained prompt file in `spec/revit-parity/agent-prompts/`
- ElemKind union in `packages/core/src/index.ts` — all element types registered here
- Element union (line 1122+) — massive inline union type for all project elements
- `SavedViewElem` — standalone exported type (not inline in Element union) at line ~3948
- `orbitCameraPoseMm` from `useBimStore` — gives current camera position/target/up in mm; used for saving 3D views
- `reduceWalkthrough`/`WalkthroughState` in `toolGrammar.ts` — grammar exists, emits `createCameraPath` effect
- `PbContextMenu` in `ProjectBrowser.tsx` — right-click menu for view rows, needs Lock/Unlock item
- `savedViewLockedRef`/`savedViewLocked` in `Viewport.tsx` — ALREADY blocks camera when `isLocked === true`
- Pre-existing test failure: `ProjectSetupDialog.test.tsx > creates location sun settings when missing` — unrelated to wave work, pre-dates it

3. Files and Code Sections:

- **`spec/revit-parity/revit2026-parity-tracker.md`**
  - Summary Dashboard was stale; fixed and committed (`docs(tracker): sync Summary Dashboard with wave-1 reality`)
  - Removed Scale/PhaseManager/InteriorElevation from P1 gap list (all done in wave 1)
  - Downgraded model groups from P0 to P1
  - Each P1/P2 gap now has precise file-level next-step guidance

- **`spec/revit-parity/agent-prompts/WAVE2-WP-A.md` through `WAVE2-WP-G.md`**
  - 7 new wave-2 prompt files created and pushed
  - Each is self-contained with: what wave-1 built (do not rebuild), exact tasks, file paths, tests required, tracker update instructions
  - Key shared-file conflict rule stated in each: `git pull --rebase origin main` before editing `toolGrammar.ts`, `toolRegistry.ts`, `core/index.ts`, `PlanCanvas.tsx`

- **`packages/core/src/index.ts`** — PARTIALLY EDITED (session interrupted mid-implementation)
  - Added `isLocked?: boolean` to `SavedViewElem` (with JSDoc comment):
    ```ts
    export type SavedViewElem = {
      kind: 'saved_view';
      id: string;
      baseViewId: string;
      name: string;
      cameraState?: Record<string, unknown>;
      visibilityOverrides?: Record<string, unknown>;
      detailLevel?: string;
      thumbnailDataUri?: string;
      /** When true the viewport disables all camera manipulation for this view. */
      isLocked?: boolean;
    };
    ```
  - Added `isLocked?: boolean` to `UpdateSavedViewCmd`:
    ```ts
    export type UpdateSavedViewCmd = {
      type: 'update_saved_view';
      id: string;
      name?: string;
      cameraState?: Record<string, unknown>;
      visibilityOverrides?: Record<string, unknown>;
      detailLevel?: string;
      thumbnailDataUri?: string;
      isLocked?: boolean;
    };
    ```
  - Added `'camera_path'` to ElemKind union (between `'saved_view'` and `'presentation_canvas'`):
    ```ts
    | 'saved_view'
    | 'camera_path'
    | 'presentation_canvas'
    ```
  - Added new types after `SavedViewElem` definition (around line 3961):
    ```ts
    export type WalkthroughKeyframe = {
      positionMm: { x: number; y: number; z: number };
      targetMm: { x: number; y: number; z: number };
      fovDeg: number;
      /** Playback time in seconds from the start of the path. */
      timeSec: number;
    };

    export type CameraPathElem = {
      kind: 'camera_path';
      id: string;
      name: string;
      keyframes: WalkthroughKeyframe[];
    };

    export type CreateCameraPathCmd = {
      type: 'create_camera_path';
      id: string;
      name: string;
      keyframes: WalkthroughKeyframe[];
    };
    ```

- **`packages/web/src/Viewport.tsx`** (READ ONLY, not yet edited)
  - Lock behavior already implemented at lines 583, 632-633, 2756, 3232, 5702-5710:
    ```ts
    const savedViewLockedRef = useRef(false);
    const savedViewLocked = activeSavedView?.isLocked === true;
    savedViewLockedRef.current = savedViewLocked;
    // ...at line 2756: if (savedViewLockedRef.current) return; // blocks pan
    // ...at line 3232: if (savedViewLockedRef.current) return; // blocks orbit
    // ...at line 5702-5710: lock badge rendered
    ```
  - `Direct3dAuthoringTool` union (line 251-268): `'walkthrough'` is NOT in it
  - `orbitRigApiRef` (line 558-564): only has `applyViewpointMm`, not a getter
  - Keyboard handler at line 3565: `document.addEventListener('keydown', onKey)` — walkthrough Enter/Escape needs to go in `onKey`
  - `DIRECT_3D_AUTHORING_TOOLS` set (line 301+): walkthrough should NOT be added here; needs own handler in pointerup
  - `onSemanticCommandRef.current?.(cmd)` pattern at line 651-697: how to dispatch commands from Viewport

- **`packages/web/src/workspace/Workspace.tsx`** (READ ONLY)
  - `commitSave3dViewWithName` at line 2878 shows how `orbitCameraPoseMm` is used to build camera state:
    ```ts
    cameraState: {
      positionMm: orbitCameraPoseMm.position,
      targetMm: orbitCameraPoseMm.target,
      upMm: orbitCameraPoseMm.up,
      fovDeg: 60,
    }
    ```
  - `PhaseManagerDialog` wiring pattern (lines 127, 1041, 4148-4194): `phaseManagerOpen` state + `setPhaseManagerOpen` + dialog mount at bottom of Workspace render

- **`packages/web/src/workspace/project/ProjectBrowser.tsx`** (READ ONLY)
  - `ProjectBrowserProps` (lines 2063-2073): needs `onToggleLockView?: (viewId: string) => void` added
  - `PbContextMenu` function (lines 2757-2871): add `onLockToggle?: () => void` prop + button
  - Context menu usage (lines 2518-2545): needs to detect if element is `saved_view` and pass lock state + toggle
  - `CtxMenu` type (line 2075): `{ viewId: string; x: number; y: number }` — may need `isSavedView?: boolean; isLocked?: boolean` added
  - `viewRows` includes both `viewpoint` and `saved_view` kinds (line 2133-2137)

- **`packages/web/src/tools/toolGrammar.ts`** (READ ONLY)
  - `WalkthroughKeyframeCapture` (lines 2486-2491):
    ```ts
    export interface WalkthroughKeyframeCapture {
      positionMm: { x: number; y: number; z: number };
      targetMm: { x: number; y: number; z: number };
      fovDeg: number;
      timeSec: number;
    }
    ```
  - `reduceWalkthrough` (lines 2511-2535): emits `createCameraPath: { name, keyframes }` effect on commit with ≥2 keyframes
  - `'walkthrough'` ToolId exists in toolRegistry.ts (line 98, 785-793)

- **`packages/web/src/state/storeTypes.ts`**
  - `orbitCameraPoseMm` shape (lines 306-310):
    ```ts
    orbitCameraPoseMm: {
      position: { xMm: number; yMm: number; zMm: number };
      target: { xMm: number; yMm: number; zMm: number };
      up: { xMm: number; yMm: number; zMm: number };
    } | null;
    ```

4. Errors and Fixes:

- **git pull --rebase failed** with "You have unstaged changes": Fixed by `git stash` first, then pull and rebase
- **Tracker Summary Dashboard was stale**: Wave-1 agents completed Scale, PhaseManager, InteriorElevation tool/symbol — but dashboard still listed them as gaps. Fixed by rewriting the dashboard with accurate post-wave-1 state and committing.
- **WP-D left 2 items unimplemented**: Named locked 3D view and Walkthrough. User asked to implement directly. Implementation is in progress (core/index.ts edits done; Viewport.tsx, Workspace.tsx, ProjectBrowser.tsx edits not yet done).

5. Problem Solving:

- Verified wave-1 was clean: 3739→3857 passing tests (agents added ~118 tests), same 1 pre-existing failure
- Identified that `Viewport.tsx` already has the lock camera behavior (`savedViewLocked` check) but the type system didn't have `isLocked` — so TypeScript was OK via optional chaining but the field was not officially typed
- Identified that walkthrough ToolId + grammar (reduceWalkthrough) exist but are wired to nothing — no Viewport dispatch, no command handler, no playback UI
